The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Chronicle Reporter POLICE have urged drivers to stop after accidents and render first aid if necessary, following a fatal hit and run incident in Bulawayo on Thursday. According to the police, the man died on the spot along Rangemore Road in Bulawayo. “The ZRP urges all drivers to stop after accidents and render first aid where necessary; all accidents must be reported within 24 hours. On 11/02/21, an unknown pedestrian was hit by an unknown motorist along Rangemore Road, Bulawayo and died on the spot. The driver did not stop after the accident,” Tweeted the police. Last year Zimbabwe hip hop superstar was hit by a car metres away from his Luveve 5 home in Bulawayo and up until now, the perpetrator has not been caught, nearly four months later.